  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "It was recently brought to my attestation (by @nisdas) that although the `Hash` type seems clear, the default instantiation `Hash()` (32 zero bytes) is too close to `hash()` (hash of empty byte array).\r\nWe should consider renaming it to `Root` or sticking to `Bytes32`. Or, at the very least, make comparisons against `Bytes32()` or `ZERO_HASH` to avoid confusion.\r\n\r\ncc @JustinDrake You had an initial preference for `Hash` over `Root`/other as type. Are there any counter arguments against changing `Hash`? What option do you like best?\r\n",
