    "body": "> Are there any counter arguments against changing `Hash`?\r\n\r\nRenaming all `Hash` to `Root` does not work semantically everywhere (e.g. `withdrawal_credentials`, `proof`, `randao_mixes`, `hash`, `block_hash`). We could name the roots to `Root`s, and leave the non-roots as `bytes32`.\r\n\r\n> the default instantiation `Hash()` (32 zero bytes) is too close to `hash()` (hash of empty byte array)\r\n\r\nProbably the easiest fix for that is to reintroduce the `ZERO_HASH` constant.\r\n\r\n> What option do you like best?\r\n\r\nI'd say either status quo or reintroducing the `ZERO_HASH` constant is best.",
